# Footer Schema Structure

The footer section of the application is now managed as a **frontend component** with hardcoded data located in `frontend/src/constants/footer.ts`.

**Note:** The backend footer API structure remains intact in Strapi but is no longer used by the frontend.

## Frontend Implementation

### Constants File

Footer data is defined in: `frontend/src/constants/footer.ts`

The `FOOTER_DATA` constant contains all footer content:

```typescript
export interface FooterLink {
  title: string;
  url: string;
}

export interface FooterColumn {
  header: string;
  links: FooterLink[];
}

export interface ContactInfo {
  phone: string;
  whatsapp: string | null;
  instagram: string | null;
  telegram: string | null;
}

export interface FooterData {
  customerSupport: string;
  first: FooterColumn;
  second: FooterColumn;
  third: FooterColumn;
  contactUs: ContactInfo;
  storeLocations: string;
}
```

### Schema Structure

The footer consists of the following main sections:

#### Column Sections (First, Second, Third)

Each column in the footer has:
- `header`: The title of the column
- `links`: An array of link objects containing:
  - `title`: Display text for the link
  - `url`: Target path for the link

#### Contact Us Section

Contains contact information:
- `phone`: Phone number for customer support
- `whatsapp`: WhatsApp contact (nullable)
- `instagram`: Instagram profile link (nullable)
- `telegram`: Telegram contact (nullable)

#### Customer Support

Text describing customer support hours and availability.

#### Store Locations

Text describing physical store locations.

## Component Structure

- **Main Component**: `frontend/src/components/PLP/Footer/index.tsx` (Server Component)
- **Sub-components**:
  - `UserAccountSection.tsx` - First column (Account links)
  - `QuickAccessSection.tsx` - Second column (Quick access links)
  - `CustomerServiceSection.tsx` - Third column (Customer service links + support text)
  - `StoresSection.tsx` - Store locations and contact info
  - `LogoSection.tsx` - Logo display

All components are now server components (no client-side data fetching).

## Updating Footer Content

To update the footer:

1. Edit `frontend/src/constants/footer.ts`
2. Modify the `FOOTER_DATA` constant
3. Changes will be reflected immediately (no API calls needed)

## Backend Structure (Unused)

The backend footer API structure remains in Strapi but is not used:

- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/footer?populate[0]=First.Links&populate[1]=Second.Links&populate[2]=Third.Links&populate[3]=ContactUs`
- **Content Type**: `footer` (Single Type)
- **Components**: `footer.footer-section`, `footer.contact-us`

The Super Admin footer management pages have been disabled with notices directing developers to edit the constants file instead.

## Benefits

- No API calls on page load (better performance)
- Footer renders immediately (no loading state)
- Simpler component structure (no async data fetching)
- Easier to maintain (data in one place)
- Backend structure preserved for future use if needed

